                    Article I  
                </h2>   
                <h3> 
                    Incorporation  
                </h3>            
            </div>
            <ol>
                <li>
                Section 1. The name of this organization shall be “Charleston Area Justice Ministry (CAJM)”.
                </li>
                <li>
                Section 2. CAJM shall be a non-profit corporation, established in accordance with section 501 (c)(3) of the Tax Code of the Internal Revenue Service and the laws of the State of South Carolina.
                </li>
                <li>
                Section 3. Authority is vested in the Annual Assembly (“Annual Assembly”), which is the ultimate decision-making body for the organization which delegates authority and responsibility between meetings to the Leadership Senate.
